HEADWORD: lespedeza
<hw>lespedeza</hw> <pos>n.</pos> <def>Any shrubby or herbaceous plant of
the genus <gen>Lespedeza</gen>, widely used for forage, soil
improvement, and especially hay in the Southern U.S.</def>⟦br⟧
<syn><b>Syn. --</b> bush clover.</syn>⟦br⟧
